name: Commodore 64 Disk Image
summary: An X64 file contains a disk image dumped from a Commodore 64 hard disk or floppy disk. It stores information about a Commodore 64 game or program in X64 format, which includes a 64-byte header followed by disk image data. X64 files are supported by Various emulators of Commodore 64 (C64), a popular personal computer from the 1980s.
